title: The stripping process in the interactions of accelerated N-14 ions with the nuclei of some elements.

accelerated N-14 ions with the nuclei of some elements.

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Low and Medium Energy Nucl.Reactons, Moscow 1957, p.513 (1957)

x4freetext: Magnetic analyzer was used to determine the
sign of the beta particles.
Targets made of Al, Ni, Cu, Ag, Cd, Sn, Pt, Au, and
Pb were used. The target thickness was such that the
particle energy after traversing the target did not
exceed 70 Mev.

reacs.QuantHlp: Differential c/s with respect to angle

x4freetext: No explanation of relative units is given.
N-13 were stopped in the collector made of 3.5 mu-m
lead foil. Lead collector was put into the form of a
cylindrical surface which included all angles from +
60 to -60 degrees. After irradiation the collector
was cut into equal strips for measurement of the
beta-activity decay curve.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Statistical errors and the angular spread
due to the finite size of the strips are given.
Fig.2 a

x4freetext: The number of N-13 nuclei was determined by
separation of the ten-minute activity in the lead
collectors. The efficiency of the beta particle
detection was determined by means of a radioactive
source of known intensity.
The error in determining the absolute
value of the cross section was caused principally
by lack of accurate knowledge concerning the
efficiency of detection of the beta particles.
Error of the relative measurements as
well as the energy spread due to the finite target
thickness are given.
Fig.5 from J,JET,6,459,1958
